2:
Foolish people die because they are resentful;
\q2 people whom others easily deceive—these people die because they envy others.
\q1

6:
But it is not the farmland that makes bad things happen;
\q2 troubles do not grow up from the ground like plants.
\q1

9:
He does great things, things that we cannot understand;
\q2 we cannot even count the marvelous things that he does.
\q1

10:
He sends rain on the ground;
\q2 he makes it rain on our fields.
\q1

13:
The people who think they are wise—he makes their own traps catch them;
\q2 the result is that they do not succeed.
\q1

15:
But God saves helpless people from the wicked who say evil things about them;
\q2 he saves poor people from powerful people harming them.
\q1

17:
But those whom God corrects are fortunate;
\q2 so do not despise it when God, who can do anything, disciplines you.
\q1

18:
He wounds people, but then he puts bandages on those wounds;
\q2 he hurts people, but he also heals them.
\q1

21:
God will protect you when people say false, evil things about you;
\q2 you will not be afraid when many things around you perish.
\q1

24:
You will know that things will go well for you in your home;
\q2 when you look at your livestock, you will see that they are all there.
\q1
